  "helpSupportFaqElectricityAnswer": "Long prints and high-wattage printers can add real cost. Skipping electricity usually underprices the job.",
  "helpSupportFaqRiskQuestion": "How is failure risk calculated?",
  "helpSupportFaqRiskAnswer": "Risk is applied only to base print costs like filament and electricity. It estimates expected loss from failed prints.",
  "helpSupportFaqLabourQuestion": "What is labour / processing time?",
  "helpSupportFaqLabourAnswer": "It covers preparation, cleanup, post-processing, and monitoring. Keep it on for services where your time matters.",
  "helpSupportFaqMarkupQuestion": "What is markup?",
  "helpSupportFaqMarkupAnswer": "Markup is the percentage added on top of total cost to reach your selling price. It covers margin, overhead, and profit.",
  "helpSupportFaqSetupQuestion": "What is a setup fee?",
  "helpSupportFaqSetupAnswer": "A setup fee is a fixed cost per job for calibration, machine prep, and admin. It helps small prints cover overhead.",
